The use of tight bounds and analysis of specific families of graphs suggests that it may also belong to the discrete mathematics (cs.DM) sub-category. The focus on ratios and optimization suggests that it may belong to the algorithms (cs.DS) or game theory (cs.GT) sub-categories. Finally, the use of trigonometric functions and analysis of geometric properties suggests that it may also belong to the scientific computing (cs.SI) sub-category.
